  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Aerospace Technician (Engine MRO)",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a Aerospace Technician to be part of our division. You will play a vital role in the end-to-end overhaul and maintenance of aero engines, utilizing advanced tooling and technical manuals. We value technical precision and a commitment to quality, offering a platform to apply your expertise in a high-stakes, safety-critical aviation environment</p><h2><strong>Salary & Benefits</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Basic Salary: Up to $3,300, Gross Salary: Up to $4,500++</p></li><li><p>Location: Calshot Road (Islandwide transport provided)</p></li><li><p>$250 Fixed Shift Allowance</p></li><li><p>9% Salary Increment after completing 2 weeks of training</p></li><li><p>Guaranteed Monthly Bonus + 4 to 5 months’ Performance Bonus (paid quarterly)</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Work Schedule</strong></h2><ul><li><p><strong>4-Day Work Week</strong></p></li><li><p>Morning Shift: <strong>6:30am – 4:15pm</strong></p></li><li><p>Afternoon Shift: <strong>4:00pm – 1:45am</strong></p></li></ul><h2><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Perform mechanical fitment and removal tasks using a variety of hand tools and specialized equipment.</p></li><li><p>Conduct aero engine testing and testbed operations, including the installation and removal of Engine Build Up (EBU) components and starter generators.</p></li><li><p>Utilize torque wrenches, torque meters, and manual measuring instruments to ensure components are fitted to exact specifications.</p></li><li><p>Execute safety cabling and lockwiring tasks to secure engine components according to technical manuals.</p></li><li><p>Perform electrical measurements and repairs using multi-meters and extraction/insertion repair kits.</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2><ul><li><p>At least <strong>2 years of relevant experience</strong> in the aerospace industry</p></li></ul>",
